Myanmar, Laos Sign Two Agreements 
Myanmar and Laos here today signed two agreements on drugs control and
border areas management, according to Myanma News Agency.
Chairman of the Myanmar State Law and Order Restoration Council (SLORC)
and Prime Minister Than Shwe and other Myanmar leaders as well as
visiting Lao Prime Minister Khamtay Siphandone attended the signing
ceremony.
Before the signing ceremony, Chairman of the SLORC and Prime Minister
Than Shwe met Lao Prime Minister Khamtay Siphandone and had discussions
on bilateral ties and regional issues, according to official sources.
The Lao prime minister arrived here this morning beginning his four-day
official visit to Myanmar at the invitation of Than Shwe.
It is Khamtay's second trip to Myanmar since 1992.
Than Shwe visited Laos in June 1994.
